swL2MgmtMIB.name: swL2MgmtMIB
swL2MgmtMIB.description: The Structure of Layer 2 Network Management Information for enterprise.

swL2DevInfoFrontPanelLedStatus.name: swL2DevInfoFrontPanelLedStatus
swL2DevInfoFrontPanelLedStatus.description: This object is a set of system LED indications. When log in system DES3028/DES3052 which do not support POE, the first two octets is defined as system LED. The first LED is power LED. The second LED is console LED. When log in system DES3028p/DES3052p which support POE, the first four octets are defined as system LED. The first octet is 0x02 and the second octet is 0x01 when in normal mode. Contrarily, the first octet is 0x01 and the second octet is 0x02 when in poe mode. The third octet indicates the power LED. The fourth octet indicates the console LED. The other octets are defined as follow: start on the third or fifth octets separately correspond to system support poe or system which does not support poe indicate the logical port LED (following swL2BasePort ordering). Every two bytes are presented to a port. The first byte is presentd to the Link/Activity LED. The second byte is presented to the Speed LED. Link/Activity LED : The most significant bit is used for blink/solid: 8 = The LED blinks. The second significant bit is used for link status: 1 = link fail. 2 = link pass. Speed LED : 01 = 10Mbps. 02 = 100Mbps. 03 = 1000Mbps. The four remaining bits are currently unused and must be 0.

swL2DevCtrlSystemReboot.name: swL2DevCtrlSystemReboot
swL2DevCtrlSystemReboot.description: This object indicates the agent system reboot state. The agent always returns other(1) when this object is read.

swL2DevCtrlSubnetMask.name: swL2DevCtrlSubnetMask
swL2DevCtrlSubnetMask.description: This object indicates system subnet mask.

swL2DevCtrlDefaultGateway.name: swL2DevCtrlDefaultGateway
swL2DevCtrlDefaultGateway.description: This object indicates system default gateway.

swL2DevCtrlManagementVlanId.name: swL2DevCtrlManagementVlanId
swL2DevCtrlManagementVlanId.description: This object controls which Vlan includes system ip. And the Vlan should have been created.

swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping.name: swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping
swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping.description: This object indicates layer 2 Internet Group Management Protocol (IGMP) capture function is enabled or disabled .

swL2DevCtrlCleanAllStatisticCounter.name: swL2DevCtrlCleanAllStatisticCounter
swL2DevCtrlCleanAllStatisticCounter.description: As the object is set to active, all the statistic counters will be cleared. If set to normal, do nothing.

swL2DevCtrlSnmpEnableAuthenTraps.name: swL2DevCtrlSnmpEnableAuthenTraps
swL2DevCtrlSnmpEnableAuthenTraps.description: Indicates whether the SNMP entity is permitted to generate authenticationFailure traps. The value of this object overrides any configuration information; as such, it provides a means whereby all authenticationFailure traps may be disabled. Note that it is strongly recommended that this object be stored in non-volatile memory so that it remains constant across re-initializations of the network management system.

swL2DevCtrlRmonState.name: swL2DevCtrlRmonState
swL2DevCtrlRmonState.description: This object can be enabled or disabled RMON.

swL2DevCtrlIpAutoConfig.name: swL2DevCtrlIpAutoConfig
swL2DevCtrlIpAutoConfig.description: Indicates the status of automatically getting configuration from TFTP server on device

swL2MACNotifyState.name: swL2MACNotifyState
swL2MACNotifyState.description: This object can enabled or disabled MAC Notification.

swL2MACNotifyHistorySize.name: swL2MACNotifyHistorySize
swL2MACNotifyHistorySize.description: This object indicates the history size of variation MAC in address table. The default value is 1 .

swL2MACNotifyInterval.name: swL2MACNotifyInterval
swL2MACNotifyInterval.description: This object indicates the time interval in second for trigger the MAC notify message.

swL2DevCtrlLLDPState.name: swL2DevCtrlLLDPState
swL2DevCtrlLLDPState.description: Specifies the state of the LLDP function. When this function is enabled, the switch can start to transmit LLDP packets and receive and process the LLDP packets. The specific function of each port will depend on the per port LLDP setting. For the advertisement of LLDP packets, the switch announces the information to its neighbor through ports. For the receiving of LLDP packets, the switch will learn the information from the LLDP packets advertised from the neighbor in the neighbor table.

swL2DevCtrlLLDPForwardMessageState.name: swL2DevCtrlLLDPForwardMessageState
swL2DevCtrlLLDPForwardMessageState.description: When lldp is disabled and lldp forward-message is enabled, the received LLDP Data Units packet will be forwarded.

swL2DevCtrlAsymVlanState.name: swL2DevCtrlAsymVlanState
swL2DevCtrlAsymVlanState.description: This object enables or disables the asymmetric VLAN feature of the device.

swL2IGMPSnoopingMulticastVlanState.name: swL2IGMPSnoopingMulticastVlanState
swL2IGMPSnoopingMulticastVlanState.description: This indicates the global state of the igmp-snoop multicast-vlan.

swL2DevCtrlVLANTrunkState.name: swL2DevCtrlVLANTrunkState
swL2DevCtrlVLANTrunkState.description: This indicates the global state of the VLAN trunking feature of the device.

swL2DevCtrlTelnetState.name: swL2DevCtrlTelnetState
swL2DevCtrlTelnetState.description: This object controls the Telnet status.

swL2DevAlarmNewRoot.name: swL2DevAlarmNewRoot
swL2DevAlarmNewRoot.description: When the device has become the new root of the Spanning Tree, this object decides whether to send a new root trap.

swL2DevAlarmTopologyChange.name: swL2DevAlarmTopologyChange
swL2DevAlarmTopologyChange.description: This object determines whether or not to send a trap message when the switch topology changes. If the object is enabled (3), the Topology Change trap is sent by the device when any of its configured ports transition from the Learning state to the Forwarding state, or from the Forwarding state to the Blocking state. For the same port transition, the device does not send the trap if this object value is disabled or in another state.

swL2DevAlarmLinkChange.name: swL2DevAlarmLinkChange
swL2DevAlarmLinkChange.description: This object determines whether or not to send a trap message when the link changes. If the object is enabled (3), the Link Change trap is sent by the device when any of its port links change. The device does not send the trap if this object value is disabled or in another state.

swL2PortInfoTable.name: swL2PortInfoTable
swL2PortInfoTable.description: A table that contains information about every port.

swL2PortInfoEntry.name: swL2PortInfoEntry
swL2PortInfoEntry.description: A list of information for each port of the device.

swL2PortInfoPortIndex.name: swL2PortInfoPortIndex
swL2PortInfoPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortInfoMediumType.name: swL2PortInfoMediumType
swL2PortInfoMediumType.description: This object indicates the port type: fiber or copper.

swL2PortInfoLinkStatus.name: swL2PortInfoLinkStatus
swL2PortInfoLinkStatus.description: This object indicates the port link status.

swL2PortInfoNwayStatus.name: swL2PortInfoNwayStatus
swL2PortInfoNwayStatus.description: This object indicates the port speed and duplex mode.

swL2PortCtrlTable.name: swL2PortCtrlTable
swL2PortCtrlTable.description: A table that contains control information about every port.

swL2PortCtrlEntry.name: swL2PortCtrlEntry
swL2PortCtrlEntry.description: A list of control information for each port of the device.

swL2PortCtrlPortIndex.name: swL2PortCtrlPortIndex
swL2PortCtrlPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortCtrlPortMediumType.name: swL2PortCtrlPortMediumType
swL2PortCtrlPortMediumType.description: This object indicates the port type: fiber or copper.

swL2PortCtrlAdminState.name: swL2PortCtrlAdminState
swL2PortCtrlAdminState.description: This object decides whether the port is enabled or disabled.

swL2PortCtrlNwayState.name: swL2PortCtrlNwayState
swL2PortCtrlNwayState.description: Choose the port speed, duplex mode, and N-Way function mode.

swL2PortCtrlFlowCtrlState.name: swL2PortCtrlFlowCtrlState
swL2PortCtrlFlowCtrlState.description: Set the flow control function as enabled or disabled.

swL2PortCtrlDescription.name: swL2PortCtrlDescription
swL2PortCtrlDescription.description: The object describes the ports in text.

swL2PortCtrlAddressLearning.name: swL2PortCtrlAddressLearning
swL2PortCtrlAddressLearning.description: This object decides whether the address learning is enabled or disabled.

swL2PortCtrlMACNotifyState.name: swL2PortCtrlMACNotifyState
swL2PortCtrlMACNotifyState.description: This object sets each port's MAC notification state.

swL2PortCtrlMulticastfilter.name: swL2PortCtrlMulticastfilter
swL2PortCtrlMulticastfilter.description: This object decides the multicast packet filtering mode on this port.

swL2PortCtrlMDIXState.name: swL2PortCtrlMDIXState
swL2PortCtrlMDIXState.description: This object configures the MDIX setting of the port. The value 'other' is for those entries in which MDIX is not applicable.

swL2PortErrTable.name: swL2PortErrTable
swL2PortErrTable.description: A table that contains information about the Err port.

swL2PortErrEntry.name: swL2PortErrEntry
swL2PortErrEntry.description: A list of information for the err port of the device.

swL2PortErrPortIndex.name: swL2PortErrPortIndex
swL2PortErrPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortErrPortState.name: swL2PortErrPortState
swL2PortErrPortState.description: This object decides whether the port state is enabled or disabled.

swL2PortErrPortStatus.name: swL2PortErrPortStatus
swL2PortErrPortStatus.description: This object decides whether the PortStatus is err-disabled.

swL2PortErrPortReason.name: swL2PortErrPortReason
swL2PortErrPortReason.description: This object indicates the module which disabled the port.

swL2PortErrDescription.name: swL2PortErrDescription
swL2PortErrDescription.description: The object describes the ports in text.

swL2QOSBandwidthControlEntry.name: swL2QOSBandwidthControlEntry
swL2QOSBandwidthControlEntry.description: A list of information contained in swL2QOSBandwidthControlTable.

swL2QOSBandwidthRxRate.name: swL2QOSBandwidthRxRate
swL2QOSBandwidthRxRate.description: Indicates the RX Rate(Mbit/sec) of the specifed port. A value of 1024000 means no limit.

swL2QOSBandwidthTxRate.name: swL2QOSBandwidthTxRate
swL2QOSBandwidthTxRate.description: Indicates the TX Rate(Mbit/sec) of the specifed port. A value of 1024000 means no limit.

swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusRxRate.name: swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusRxRate
swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusRxRate.description: The Rx Rate value comes from the RADIUS server, If an 802.1X port is authenticated, this value will overwrite the locally configured Rx Rate.

swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusTxRate.name: swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusTxRate
swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusTxRate.description: The Tx Rate value comes from the RADIUS server, If an 802.1X port is authenticated, this value will overwrite the locally configured Tx Rate.

swL2QOSSchedulingEntry.name: swL2QOSSchedulingEntry
swL2QOSSchedulingEntry.description: A list of information contained in the swL2QOSSchedulingTable.

swL2QOSSchedulingMechanism.name: swL2QOSSchedulingMechanism
swL2QOSSchedulingMechanism.description: Indicates the mechanism of QOS scheduling.

swL2QOSSchedulingMechanismCtrl.name: swL2QOSSchedulingMechanismCtrl
swL2QOSSchedulingMechanismCtrl.description: This object can control QOS scheduling Mechanism.

swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityEntry.name: swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityEntry
swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityEntry.description: A list of information contained in the swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityTable.

swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityClass.name: swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityClass
swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityClass.description: The number of the switch's hardware priority queue. The switch has four hardware priority queues available. They are numbered between 0 (the lowest priority) and 3 (the highest priority).

swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriorityEntry.name: swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriorityEntry
swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriorityEntry.description: A list of information contained in the swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriorityTable.

swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriority.name: swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriority
swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriority.description: The priority value to assign to untagged packets received by the switch ports on the switch.

swL2QOS8021pRadiusPriority.name: swL2QOS8021pRadiusPriority
swL2QOS8021pRadiusPriority.description: Indicates the value of 802.1p comes from RADIUS server. If an 802.1X port is authenticated, this value will overwrite the local configured value.

swPortTrunkMaxEntries.name: swPortTrunkMaxEntries
swPortTrunkMaxEntries.description: The max entries of the swPortTrunkTable

swPortTrunkMaxPortMembers.name: swPortTrunkMaxPortMembers
swPortTrunkMaxPortMembers.description: The max number of ports allowed in a trunk.

swPortTrunkTable.name: swPortTrunkTable
swPortTrunkTable.description: This table specifies the port membership for each logical link.

swPortTrunkEntry.name: swPortTrunkEntry
swPortTrunkEntry.description: A list of information that specifies which port group forms a single logical link.

swPortTrunkIndex.name: swPortTrunkIndex
swPortTrunkIndex.description: The index of logical port trunk.

swPortTrunkMasterPort.name: swPortTrunkMasterPort
swPortTrunkMasterPort.description: The object indicates the master port number of the port trunk entry. The first port of the trunk is implicitly configured to be the master logical port. When using a Port Trunk, you can not configure the other ports of the group except the master port. Their configuration must be the same as the master port (e.g. speed, duplex, enabled/disabled, flow control, and so on).

swPortTrunkPortList.name: swPortTrunkPortList
swPortTrunkPortList.description: Indicate member ports of a logical trunk.

swPortTrunkType.name: swPortTrunkType
swPortTrunkType.description: This object indicates the type of this entry.

swPortTrunkActivePort.name: swPortTrunkActivePort
swPortTrunkActivePort.description: This object indicates the active ports of this entry.

swPortTrunkState.name: swPortTrunkState
swPortTrunkState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. when the state is CreatAndGo (4),the type of trunk is static (1); when the state is CreatAndWait (5), the type of trunk is lacp(2).

swPortTrunkFloodingPort.name: swPortTrunkFloodingPort
swPortTrunkFloodingPort.description: The flooding port of every trunk.

swL2TrunkAlgorithm.name: swL2TrunkAlgorithm
swL2TrunkAlgorithm.description: This object configures part of the packet to be examined by the switch when selecting the egress port for transmitting load-sharing data.

swL2TrunkLACPPortTable.name: swL2TrunkLACPPortTable
swL2TrunkLACPPortTable.description: This table specifies which port group a set of ports (up to 8) is formed into a single logical link.

swL2TrunkLACPPortEntry.name: swL2TrunkLACPPortEntry
swL2TrunkLACPPortEntry.description: A list of information specifies which port group a set of ports (up to 8) is formed into a single logical link.

swL2TrunkLACPPortIndex.name: swL2TrunkLACPPortIndex
swL2TrunkLACPPortIndex.description: The index of the logical port LACP.

swL2TrunkLACPPortState.name: swL2TrunkLACPPortState
swL2TrunkLACPPortState.description: The state of the logical port LACP.

swL2TrunkVLANTable.name: swL2TrunkVLANTable
swL2TrunkVLANTable.description: This table is used to manage the VLAN trunking feature of the device.

swL2TrunkVLANEntry.name: swL2TrunkVLANEntry
swL2TrunkVLANEntry.description: This object is used to configure the VLAN trunking settings for each port.

swL2TrunkVLANPort.name: swL2TrunkVLANPort
swL2TrunkVLANPort.description: This object indicates the port being configured.

swL2TrunkVLANState.name: swL2TrunkVLANState
swL2TrunkVLANState.description: The state of the logical port LACP.

swPortMirrorRxPortList.name: swPortMirrorRxPortList
swPortMirrorRxPortList.description: This object indicates the Rx port list of ports to be sniffed.

swPortMirrorTxPortList.name: swPortMirrorTxPortList
swPortMirrorTxPortList.description: This object indicates the Tx port list of ports to be sniffed.

swPortMirrorTargetPort.name: swPortMirrorTargetPort
swPortMirrorTargetPort.description: This object indicates the switch whose port will sniff another port. A trunk port member cannot be configured as a target Snooping port. The port number is the sequential (logical) number which is also applied to the bridge MIB, etc.

swPortMirrorState.name: swPortMirrorState
swPortMirrorState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL2IGMPMaxSupportedVlans.name: swL2IGMPMaxSupportedVlans
swL2IGMPMaxSupportedVlans.description: The maximum number of VLANs in the layer 2 IGMP control table (swL2IGMPCtrlTable).

swL2IGMPMaxIpGroupNumPerVlan.name: swL2IGMPMaxIpGroupNumPerVlan
swL2IGMPMaxIpGroupNumPerVlan.description: The maximum number of multicast IP groups per VLAN in the layer 2 IGMP information table (swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable).

swL2IGMPCtrlTable.name: swL2IGMPCtrlTable
swL2IGMPCtrlTable.description: The table controls the VLAN's IGMP function. Its scale depends on the current VLAN state (swL2VlanInfoStatus). If the VLAN mode is disabled, there is only one entry in the table, with index 1. If VLAN is in Port-Based or 802.1q mode, the number of entries can be up to 12, with an index range from 1 to 12.

swL2IGMPCtrlEntry.name: swL2IGMPCtrlEntry
swL2IGMPCtrlEntry.description: An entry in IGMP control table (swL2IGMPCtrlTable). The entry is effective only when IGMP captures the switch (swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping) is enabled.

swL2IGMPCtrlVid.name: swL2IGMPCtrlVid
swL2IGMPCtrlVid.description: This object indicates the IGMP control entry's VLAN ID. If VLAN is disabled, the VID is always 0 and cannot be changed by management users. If VLAN is in Port-Based mode, the VID is arranged from 1 to 12, fixed form. If VLAN is in 802.1q mode, the VID setting can vary from 1 to 4094 by management user, and the VID in each entry must be unique in the IGMP Control Table.

swL2IGMPQueryInterval.name: swL2IGMPQueryInterval
swL2IGMPQueryInterval.description: The frequency at which IGMP Host-Query packets are transmitted on this switch.

swL2IGMPMaxResponseTime.name: swL2IGMPMaxResponseTime
swL2IGMPMaxResponseTime.description: The maximum query response time on this switch.

swL2IGMPRobustness.name: swL2IGMPRobustness
swL2IGMPRobustness.description: The Robustness Variable allows tuning for the expected packet loss on a subnet. If a subnet is expected to be lossy, the Robustness Variable may be increased. IGMP is robust to (Robustness Variable-1) packet losses.

swL2IGMPLastMemberQueryInterval.name: swL2IGMPLastMemberQueryInterval
swL2IGMPLastMemberQueryInterval.description: The Last Member Query Interval is the Max Response Time inserted into Group-Specific Queries sent in response to Leave Group messages, and is also the amount of time between Group-Specific Query messages.

swL2IGMPHostTimeout.name: swL2IGMPHostTimeout
swL2IGMPHostTimeout.description: The timer value for sending IGMP query packets when none was sent by the host in the LAN. The timer works on a per-VLAN basis. Our device will be activated to send the query message if the timer expires. Please reference RFC2236-1997.

swL2IGMPRouteTimeout.name: swL2IGMPRouteTimeout
swL2IGMPRouteTimeout.description: The Router Timeout is how long a host must wait after hearing a Query before it may send any IGMPv2 messages.

swL2IGMPLeaveTimer.name: swL2IGMPLeaveTimer
swL2IGMPLeaveTimer.description: When a querier receives a Leave Group message for a group that has group members on the reception interface, it sends Group-Specific Queries every swL2IGMPLeaveTimer to the group being left.

swL2IGMPQueryState.name: swL2IGMPQueryState
swL2IGMPQueryState.description: This object decides if the IGMP query is enabled or disabled.

swL2IGMPCurrentState.name: swL2IGMPCurrentState
swL2IGMPCurrentState.description: This object indicates the current IGMP query state.

swL2IGMPCtrlState.name: swL2IGMPCtrlState
swL2IGMPCtrlState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other (1) - This entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. disable (2) - IGMP function is disabled for this entry. enable (3) - IGMP function is enabled for this entry.

swL2IGMPDynIPMultVlanState.name: swL2IGMPDynIPMultVlanState
swL2IGMPDynIPMultVlanState.description: This object is used to disable or enable the dynamic IP multicast feature in this VLAN.

swL2IGMPDynIPMultVlanAge.name: swL2IGMPDynIPMultVlanAge
swL2IGMPDynIPMultVlanAge.description: This object is used to enable or disable aging on the dynamic IP multicast entry in this VLAN.

swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable.name: swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable
swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable.description: The table contains the number of current IGMP query packets which are captured by this device, as well as the IGMP query packets sent by the device.

swL2IGMPQueryInfoEntry.name: swL2IGMPQueryInfoEntry
swL2IGMPQueryInfoEntry.description: Information about current IGMP query information, provided that swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping and swL2IGMPCtrState of associated VLAN entry are all enabled.

swL2IGMPInfoVid.name: swL2IGMPInfoVid
swL2IGMPInfoVid.description: This object indicates the VID of the associated IGMP info table entry. It follows swL2IGMPCtrlVid in the associated entry of IGMP control table (swL2IGMPCtrlTable).

swL2IGMPInfoQueryCount.name: swL2IGMPInfoQueryCount
swL2IGMPInfoQueryCount.description: This object indicates the number of query packets received since the IGMP function enabled, on a per-VLAN basis.

swL2IGMPInfoTxQueryCount.name: swL2IGMPInfoTxQueryCount
swL2IGMPInfoTxQueryCount.description: This object indicates the send count of IGMP query messages, on a per-VLAN basis. In case of the IGMP timer expiring, the switch sends IGMP query packets to related VLAN member ports and increment this object by 1.

swL2IGMPInfoTable.name: swL2IGMPInfoTable
swL2IGMPInfoTable.description: The table containing current IGMP information which was captured by this device, provided that swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping and swL2IGMPCtrlState of associated VLAN entry are all enabled. Note that the priority of IGMP table entries is lower than Filtering Table, i.e. if there is a table hash collision between the entries of IGMP Table and Filtering Table inside the switch H/W address table, then Filtering Table entry overwrite the colliding entry of IGMP Table. Also see swL2FilterMgmt description.

swL2IGMPInfoEntry.name: swL2IGMPInfoEntry
swL2IGMPInfoEntry.description: Information about current IGMP information which was captured by this device, provided that swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping and swL2IGMPCtrlState of associated VLAN entry are all enabled.

swL2IGMPVid.name: swL2IGMPVid
swL2IGMPVid.description: This object indicates the VID of an individual IGMP table entry. It shows the VID of IGMP report information captured on the network.

swL2IGMPGroupIpAddr.name: swL2IGMPGroupIpAddr
swL2IGMPGroupIpAddr.description: This object is the identify group IP address which is captured from IGMP packet, on a per-VLAN basis.

swL2IGMPMacAddr.name: swL2IGMPMacAddr
swL2IGMPMacAddr.description: This object identifies the MAC address which is corresponding to swL2IGMPGroupIpAddr, on a per-VLAN basis.

swL2IGMPPortMap.name: swL2IGMPPortMap
swL2IGMPPortMap.description: This object indicates which ports belong to the same multicast group, on a per-VLAN basis. Each multicast group has an octet string to indicate the port map. The most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the switch is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0' (Note that the setting of the bit corresponding to the port from which a frame is received is irrelevant). The 4 octets represent one unit port according to its logic port. If the unit is less than 32 ports, the other port will just fill this value with zeros.

swL2IGMPIpGroupReportCount.name: swL2IGMPIpGroupReportCount
swL2IGMPIpGroupReportCount.description: This object indicates how many report packets were received by our device corresponding with this entry that has the IGMP function enabled, on a per-VLAN basis.

swL2IGMPRouterPortTable.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortTable
swL2IGMPRouterPortTable.description: The information of the router port table.

swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanid.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanid
swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanid.description: This object indicates the VLAN ID of the router port entry.

swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanName.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanName
swL2IGMPRouterPortVlanName.description: This object indicates the VLAN name of the router port entry.

swL2IGMPRouterPortStaticPortList.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortStaticPortList
swL2IGMPRouterPortStaticPortList.description: This object indicates the static portlist of the router port entry.

swL2IGMPRouterPortDynamicPortList.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortDynamicPortList
swL2IGMPRouterPortDynamicPortList.description: This object indicates the dynamic portlist of the router port entry.

swL2IGMPRouterPortForbiddenPortList.name: swL2IGMPRouterPortForbiddenPortList
swL2IGMPRouterPortForbiddenPortList.description: This object indicates the forbidden portlist of the router port entry.

swL2IGMPAccessAuthTable.name: swL2IGMPAccessAuthTable
swL2IGMPAccessAuthTable.description: This table is used to manage the IGMP Access Authentication configurations of the device.

swL2IGMPAccessAuthEntry.name: swL2IGMPAccessAuthEntry
swL2IGMPAccessAuthEntry.description: A list of manageable entities for IGMP Access Authentication. The configuration is done per port.

swL2IGMPAccessAuthPort.name: swL2IGMPAccessAuthPort
swL2IGMPAccessAuthPort.description: The index of the swL2IGMPAccessAuthTable. This object corresponds to the port being configured.

swL2IGMPAccessAuthState.name: swL2IGMPAccessAuthState
swL2IGMPAccessAuthState.description: This object denotes the status of IGMP Access Authentication of the port.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanTable.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanTable
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanTable.description: Information about the IGMP snooping multicast VLAN table.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanid.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanid
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanid.description: This object indicates the VLAN ID of the IGMP snooping multicast VLAN entry.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanName.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanName
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanName.description: This object indicates the VLAN name of the IGMP snooping multicast VLAN entry.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanSourcePort.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanSourcePort
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanSourcePort.description: This object indicates the port list of the source ports of the IGMP snooping multicast VLAN. The source ports will be set as tag ports of the VLAN entry and the IGMP control messages received from the member ports will be forwarded to the source ports.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanMemberPort.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanMemberPort
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanMemberPort.description: This object indicates the port list of the member ports of the IGMP snooping multicast VLAN. The source ports will be set as untagged ports of the VLAN entry and the IGMP control messages received from the member ports will be forwarded to the source ports.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanTagMemberPort.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanTagMemberPort
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanTagMemberPort.description: This object indicates the port list of the tag member ports of the IGMP snooping multicast VLAN.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanState.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanState
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanState.description: This object can be used to enable or disable the IGMP snooping multicast VLAN.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanReplaceSourceIp.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanReplaceSourceIp
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanReplaceSourceIp.description: The replacement source IP of this multicast VLAN.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRowStatus.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRowStatus
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRemoveAllMcastAddrL.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRemoveAllMcastAddrListAction
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRemoveAllMcastAddrL.description: This object indicates whether to remove all the multicast address lists from the IGMP multicast VLAN or not.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanUntagSourcePort.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanUntagSourcePort
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanUntagSourcePort.description: This object indicates the untagged member ports to add to the multicast VLAN.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRemapPriority.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRemapPriority
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanRemapPriority.description: The priority value (0 to 7) to be associated with the data traffic to be forwarded on the multicast VLAN. When set to 8, the packet's original priority will be used.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanReplacePriority.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanReplacePriority
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanReplacePriority.description: Specifies that a packet's priority will be changed by the switch based on the remap priority. This flag will only take effect when remap priority is set.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupTable.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupTable
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupTable.description: The table containing the IGMP snooping multicast VLAN group information

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupEntry.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupEntry
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupEntry.description: Information about the current IGMP snooping multicast VLAN group.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupVid.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupVid
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupVid.description: This object indicates the VID of the IGMP snooping multicast VLAN group.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupFromIp.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupFromIp
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupFromIp.description: Specifies the multicast address list for this VLAN.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupToIp.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupToIp
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupToIp.description: Specifies the multicast address list for this VLAN.

swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupStatus.name: swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupStatus
swL2IGMPMulticastVlanGroupStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL2IGMPv3Table.name: swL2IGMPv3Table
swL2IGMPv3Table.description: This table contains the IGMP snooping V3 information.

swL2IGMPv3Entry.name: swL2IGMPv3Entry
swL2IGMPv3Entry.description: Information about the current IGMP snooping V3.

swL2IGMPv3SourceIPAddr.name: swL2IGMPv3SourceIPAddr
swL2IGMPv3SourceIPAddr.description: This object identifies the source IP addresses from the group where they were captured from. IGMP packets, on a per-VLAN basis.

swL2IGMPv3Forwarding.name: swL2IGMPv3Forwarding
swL2IGMPv3Forwarding.description: This object identifies if the packets from the source IP addresses are forwarding or not.

swL2IGMPv3ExpireTimer.name: swL2IGMPv3ExpireTimer
swL2IGMPv3ExpireTimer.description: This object identifies the leaving times of the source time.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupTable.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupTable
swIGMPSnoopingGroupTable.description: The table contains the current IGMP snooping group information captured by the device.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupEntry.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupEntry
swIGMPSnoopingGroupEntry.description: Information about the current IGMP snooping group information which has been captured by the device.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupVid.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupVid
swIGMPSnoopingGroupVid.description: This object indicates the VID of the individual IGMP snooping group table entry.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupGroupAddr.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupGroupAddr
swIGMPSnoopingGroupGroupAddr.description: This object identifies the group IP address which has been captured from the IGMP packet, on a per-VLAN basis.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupSourceAddr.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupSourceAddr
swIGMPSnoopingGroupSourceAddr.description: This object identifies the source addresses.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupIncludePortMap.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupIncludePortMap
swIGMPSnoopingGroupIncludePortMap.description: This object indicates the port list under INCLUDE mode.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupExcludePortMap.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupExcludePortMap
swIGMPSnoopingGroupExcludePortMap.description: This object indicates the port list under EXCLUDE mode.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupReportCount.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupReportCount
swIGMPSnoopingGroupReportCount.description: This object indicates how many report packets were received by our device corresponding with this entry that has the IGMP function enabled, on a per-group basis.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupUpTime.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupUpTime
swIGMPSnoopingGroupUpTime.description: This object indicates how long since the group was detected.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupExpiryTime.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupExpiryTime
swIGMPSnoopingGroupExpiryTime.description: This object indicates the time left before this group will be aged out.

swIGMPSnoopingGroupRouterPorts.name: swIGMPSnoopingGroupRouterPorts
swIGMPSnoopingGroupRouterPorts.description: This object indicates the port number of the router ports.

swL2IGMPDynIPMultMaxEntry.name: swL2IGMPDynIPMultMaxEntry
swL2IGMPDynIPMultMaxEntry.description: This object specifies the maximum number of entries which can be learned by dynamic IP multicast.

swL2IGMPSnoopingClearDynIpMultVID.name: swL2IGMPSnoopingClearDynIpMultVID
swL2IGMPSnoopingClearDynIpMultVID.description: This object indicates the VLAN identifier where the data driven entries will be removed from.

swL2IGMPSnoopingClearDynIpMultIP.name: swL2IGMPSnoopingClearDynIpMultIP
swL2IGMPSnoopingClearDynIpMultIP.description: This object indicates the IP address of the IGMP snooping group from which the data driven entries will be removed.

swL2IGMPSnoopingClearDynIpMultAction.name: swL2IGMPSnoopingClearDynIpMultAction
swL2IGMPSnoopingClearDynIpMultAction.description: Setting this object will clear the data driven entries. all - Remove all learned data driven groups. VLAN - Clear all data driven entries in the VLAN specified in swIGMPSnoopingClearDynIpMultVID. group - Clear the group with the address specified in swL2IGMPSnoopingClearDynIpMultIP in the VLAN specified in swIGMPSnoopingClearDynIpMultVID.

swL2TrafficSegTable.name: swL2TrafficSegTable
swL2TrafficSegTable.description: This table specifies the port just can forward traffic to the specific port list.

swL2TrafficSegEntry.name: swL2TrafficSegEntry
swL2TrafficSegEntry.description: A list of information specifies the port with its traffic forward list.

swL2TrafficSegPort.name: swL2TrafficSegPort
swL2TrafficSegPort.description: The port number of the logical port.

swL2TrafficSegForwardPorts.name: swL2TrafficSegForwardPorts
swL2TrafficSegForwardPorts.description: The port list that the specific port can forward traffic.

swL2PortSecurityControlTable.name: swL2PortSecurityControlTable
swL2PortSecurityControlTable.description: The port security feature controls the address leaning capability and the traffic forwarding decision. Each port can have this function enabled or disabled. When it is enabled and a number is given said N, which allows N addresses to be learned at this port, the first N learned addresses are locked at this port as a static entry. When the learned address number reaches N, any incoming packet without learned source addresses are discarded (e.g. dropped) and no more new addresses can be learned at this port.

swL2PortSecurityControlEntry.name: swL2PortSecurityControlEntry
swL2PortSecurityControlEntry.description: A list of information contained in the swL2PortSecurityControlTable.

swL2PortSecurityPortIndex.name: swL2PortSecurityPortIndex
swL2PortSecurityPortIndex.description: Indicates a secured port to lock address learning.

swL2PortSecurityMaxLernAddr.name: swL2PortSecurityMaxLernAddr
swL2PortSecurityMaxLernAddr.description: Indicates the allowable number of addresses to be learned at this port.

swL2PortSecurityMode.name: swL2PortSecurityMode
swL2PortSecurityMode.description: Indicates the mode of locking address. In deleteOnTimeout (3) mode - the locked addresses can be aged out after the aging timer expires. In this mode, when the locked address is aged out, the number of addresses that can be learned has to be increased by one. In deleteOnReset (4) mode - never age out the locked addresses unless restarting the system to prevent port movement or intrusion.

swL2PortSecurityAdmState.name: swL2PortSecurityAdmState
swL2PortSecurityAdmState.description: Indicates an administration state of locking address.

swL2PortSecurityTrapLogState.name: swL2PortSecurityTrapLogState
swL2PortSecurityTrapLogState.description: When enabled (2), whenever there's a new MAC that violates the pre-defined port security configuration, a trap will be sent out and the relevant information will be logged in the system.

swL2PortSecurityDelPort.name: swL2PortSecurityDelPort
swL2PortSecurityDelPort.description: Indicates the port. 0 means the function dose not work now.

swL2CosPriorityTable.name: swL2CosPriorityTable
swL2CosPriorityTable.description: Used to show and configure per port priority-based QoS features on the switch.

swL2CosPriorityEntry.name: swL2CosPriorityEntry
swL2CosPriorityEntry.description: A list of information contained in the swL2CosPriorityTable.

swL2CosPriorityPort.name: swL2CosPriorityPort
swL2CosPriorityPort.description: The port number of CoS Priority.

swL2CosPriorityPortPRI.name: swL2CosPriorityPortPRI
swL2CosPriorityPortPRI.description: Indicates the port-priority state for CoS.

swL2CosPriorityEtherPRI.name: swL2CosPriorityEtherPRI
swL2CosPriorityEtherPRI.description: Enable Ethernet frame based priority. When set ether8021p (2), enable 802.1p QoS; When set macBase (3), enable MAC-based QoS; When set disable (1), disable Ethernet frame based priority.

swL2CosPriorityIpPRI.name: swL2CosPriorityIpPRI
swL2CosPriorityIpPRI.description: Enable IP priority QoS. When set tos (2), enable TOS based QoS; When set dscp (3), enable DSCP based QoS; When set disable (1), disable IP priority QoS.

swL2CosPriorityNone.name: swL2CosPriorityNone
swL2CosPriorityNone.description: When read, it always returns invalid (2); when write valid (1), it disables all priority in this table.

swL2CosPortPRITable.name: swL2CosPortPRITable
swL2CosPortPRITable.description: Used to show port-to-class mappings and map specific port to one of the hardware queues available on the switch.

swL2CosPortPRIEntry.name: swL2CosPortPRIEntry
swL2CosPortPRIEntry.description: A list of information contained in the swL2CosPortPRITable.

swL2CosPortPRIClass.name: swL2CosPortPRIClass
swL2CosPortPRIClass.description: The number of the switch's hardware priority queue. The switch has 4 hardware priority queues available. They are numbered between 0 (the lowest priority queue) and 3 (the highest priority queue). If you want to set one, you must have administrator privileges. And you can set a value of 0 or 3 only, you can't set a value 1 or 2.

swL2CosMacBasePRITable.name: swL2CosMacBasePRITable
swL2CosMacBasePRITable.description: Used to show MAC priority map to traffic class and map the destination MAC address in incoming packet to one of the hardware queues available on the switch.

swL2CosMacBasePRIEntry.name: swL2CosMacBasePRIEntry
swL2CosMacBasePRIEntry.description: A list of information contained in the swL2CosMacBasePRITable.

swL2CosMacBasePRIClass.name: swL2CosMacBasePRIClass
swL2CosMacBasePRIClass.description: The number of the switch's hardware priority queue. The switch has 4 hardware priority queues available. They are numbered between 0 (the lowest priority queue) and 3 (the highest priority queue). If you want to set one, you must have administrator privileges.

swL2CosTosPRITable.name: swL2CosTosPRITable
swL2CosTosPRITable.description: Used to show TOS value to traffic class mapping and map the TOS value in the IP header of incoming packet to one of the four hardware queues available on the switch.

swL2CosTosPRIEntry.name: swL2CosTosPRIEntry
swL2CosTosPRIEntry.description: A list of information contained in the swL2CosTosPRITable.

swL2CosTosPRIClass.name: swL2CosTosPRIClass
swL2CosTosPRIClass.description: The number of the switch's hardware priority queue. The switch has 4 hardware priority queues available. They are numbered between 0 (the lowest priority queue) and 3 (the highest priority queue). If you want to set one, you must have administrator privileges.

swL2CosDscpPRITable.name: swL2CosDscpPRITable
swL2CosDscpPRITable.description: Used to show DSCP value to traffic class mapping and map the DSCP value in the IP header of incoming packet to one of the hardware queues available on the switch.

swL2CosDscpPRIEntry.name: swL2CosDscpPRIEntry
swL2CosDscpPRIEntry.description: A list of information contained in the swL2CosDscpPRITable.

swL2CosDscpPRIClass.name: swL2CosDscpPRIClass
swL2CosDscpPRIClass.description: The number of the switch's hardware priority queue. The switch has 4 hardware priority queues available. They are numbered between 0 (the lowest priority queue) and 3 (the highest priority queue). If you want to set one, you must have administrator privileges.

swL2DhcpRelayState.name: swL2DhcpRelayState
swL2DhcpRelayState.description: This object indicates whether the DHCP relay function is enabled or disabled.

swL2DhcpRelayHopCount.name: swL2DhcpRelayHopCount
swL2DhcpRelayHopCount.description: This object indicates the maximum number of router hops that the DHCP packets can cross.

swL2DhcpRelayTimeThreshold.name: swL2DhcpRelayTimeThreshold
swL2DhcpRelayTimeThreshold.description: This object indicates the minimum time in seconds within which the switch must relay the DHCP request. If this time is exceeded, the switch will drop the DHCP packet.

swL2DhcpRelayOption82State.name: swL2DhcpRelayOption82State
swL2DhcpRelayOption82State.description: This object indicates DHCP relay agent information option 82 function is enabled or disabled.

swL2DhcpRelayOption82Check.name: swL2DhcpRelayOption82Check
swL2DhcpRelayOption82Check.description: This object indicates the checking mechanism of DHCP relay agent information option 82 is enabled or disabled.

swL2DhcpRelayOption82Policy.name: swL2DhcpRelayOption82Policy
swL2DhcpRelayOption82Policy.description: This object indicates the reforwarding policy of DHCP relay agent information option 82. replace (1) - Replace the exiting option 82 field in messages. drop (2) - Discard messages with existing option 82 field. keep (3) - Retain the existing option 82 field in messages.

swL2DhcpRelayCtrlTable.name: swL2DhcpRelayCtrlTable
swL2DhcpRelayCtrlTable.description: This table specifies the IP address as a destination to forward (relay) DHCP packets to.

swL2DhcpRelayCtrlEntry.name: swL2DhcpRelayCtrlEntry
swL2DhcpRelayCtrlEntry.description: A list of information specifies the IP address as a destination to forward (relay) DHCP packets to.

swL2DhcpRelayCtrlInterfaceName.name: swL2DhcpRelayCtrlInterfaceName
swL2DhcpRelayCtrlInterfaceName.description: The name of the IP interface.

swL2DhcpRelayCtrlState.name: swL2DhcpRelayCtrlState
swL2DhcpRelayCtrlState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other (1) - This entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. invalid (2) - Writing this value to the object, and then the corresponding entry will be removed from the table. valid (3) - This entry resides in the table.

swL2PortSecurityViolationTrap.name: swL2PortSecurityViolationTrap
swL2PortSecurityViolationTrap.description: When the port-security trap is enabled, if there's a new MAC that violates the pre-defined port security configuration, a trap will be sent out.

swL2macNotification.name: swL2macNotification
swL2macNotification.description: This trap indicates the MAC address variations in the address table.

swL2FloodMacDetectedTrap.name: swL2FloodMacDetectedTrap
swL2FloodMacDetectedTrap.description: If theres a new flooding MAC is detected, a trap will be sent out.

swL2PortLoopOccurred.name: swL2PortLoopOccurred
swL2PortLoopOccurred.description: The trap is sent when a Port loop occurs.

swL2PortLoopRestart.name: swL2PortLoopRestart
swL2PortLoopRestart.description: The trap is sent when a Port loop restarts after the interval time.

swL2PortSecurityViolationMac.name: swL2PortSecurityViolationMac
swL2PortSecurityViolationMac.description: This object indicates the MAC address that violates the port security configuration.

swL2macNotifyInfo.name: swL2macNotifyInfo
swL2macNotifyInfo.description: This object indicates the last time reboot information.

swL2FloodMacDetectedMacVid.name: swL2FloodMacDetectedMacVid
swL2FloodMacDetectedMacVid.description: This object indicates the VID of the flooding MAC.

swL2FloodMacDetectedMacAddress.name: swL2FloodMacDetectedMacAddress
swL2FloodMacDetectedMacAddress.description: This object indicates the MAC address of the flooding MAC

swL2LoopDetectAdminState.name: swL2LoopDetectAdminState
swL2LoopDetectAdminState.description: This object indicates the loopback detection status for the system.

swL2LoopDetectInterval.name: swL2LoopDetectInterval
swL2LoopDetectInterval.description: This object indicates the interval value, the range is from 1 to 32767 seconds.

swL2LoopDetectRecoverTime.name: swL2LoopDetectRecoverTime
swL2LoopDetectRecoverTime.description: This object indicates the recover time, the range is from 60 to 1000000. The value of 0 disables the recover function.

swL2LoopDetectTrapMode.name: swL2LoopDetectTrapMode
swL2LoopDetectTrapMode.description: This object indicates the loopback detection trap mode for the system.

swL2LoopDetectPortTable.name: swL2LoopDetectPortTable
swL2LoopDetectPortTable.description: The table specifies the loopback detection function specified by port.

swL2LoopDetectPortEntry.name: swL2LoopDetectPortEntry
swL2LoopDetectPortEntry.description: The table specifies the loopback detection function specified by port.

swL2LoopDetectPortIndex.name: swL2LoopDetectPortIndex
swL2LoopDetectPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number. The range is from 1 to the maximum port number specified in the module

swL2LoopDetectPortState.name: swL2LoopDetectPortState
swL2LoopDetectPortState.description: This object indicates the loopback detection function state on the port.

swL2LoopDetectPortLoopStatus.name: swL2LoopDetectPortLoopStatus
swL2LoopDetectPortLoopStatus.description: This object indicates the port status.

swL2McastFilterTable.name: swL2McastFilterTable
swL2McastFilterTable.description: A table that contains information about the multicast filter address.

swL2McastFilterEntry.name: swL2McastFilterEntry
swL2McastFilterEntry.description: A list of multicast filter mode information for each profile ID.

swL2McastFilterGroupList.name: swL2McastFilterGroupList
swL2McastFilterGroupList.description: The multicast filter address group list.

swL2McastFilterStatus.name: swL2McastFilterStatus
swL2McastFilterStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL2McastFilterPortTable.name: swL2McastFilterPortTable
swL2McastFilterPortTable.description: A table that is used to bind port to profile ID.

swL2McastFilterPortEntry.name: swL2McastFilterPortEntry
swL2McastFilterPortEntry.description: A list of information that is used to bind port to profile ID.

swL2McastFilterPortProfileID.name: swL2McastFilterPortProfileID
swL2McastFilterPortProfileID.description: This object indicates the profile ID of this entry. When read, it is always 0. When set, 0 can not be set.

swL2McastFilterPortMaxGroupTable.name: swL2McastFilterPortMaxGroupTable
swL2McastFilterPortMaxGroupTable.description: A table that contains information about the max group number based on port.

swL2McastFilterPortMaxGroupEntry.name: swL2McastFilterPortMaxGroupEntry
swL2McastFilterPortMaxGroupEntry.description: A list of max group number information for each port.

swL2McastFilterPortMaxGroup.name: swL2McastFilterPortMaxGroup
swL2McastFilterPortMaxGroup.description: The max group numbers. The default is 256.

swL2McastFilterPortInfoTable.name: swL2McastFilterPortInfoTable
swL2McastFilterPortInfoTable.description: A table that contains information about all of the multicast groups for the ports.

swL2McastFilterPortInfoEntry.name: swL2McastFilterPortInfoEntry
swL2McastFilterPortInfoEntry.description: A list of information about all of the multicast groups for each port.

swL2McastFilterPortInfoProfileName.name: swL2McastFilterPortInfoProfileName
swL2McastFilterPortInfoProfileName.description: The multicast filter address profile Name.

swL2VlanAdvertisementTable.name: swL2VlanAdvertisementTable
swL2VlanAdvertisementTable.description: A table containing the advertisement state for each VLAN configured into the device by (local or network) management.

swL2VlanAdvertisementEntry.name: swL2VlanAdvertisementEntry
swL2VlanAdvertisementEntry.description: The advertisement state for each VLAN configured into the device.

swL2VlanIndex.name: swL2VlanIndex
swL2VlanIndex.description: The VLAN-ID or other identifier referring to this VLAN.

swL2VlanName.name: swL2VlanName
swL2VlanName.description: An administratively assigned string, which may be used to identify the VLAN.

swL2VlanAdvertiseState.name: swL2VlanAdvertiseState
swL2VlanAdvertiseState.description: This object indicates the advertise status of this VLAN entry.

swL2VlanMultiplyVlanList.name: swL2VlanMultiplyVlanList
swL2VlanMultiplyVlanList.description: This object specifies the VLAN ID List.

swL2VlanMultiplyAdvertisement.name: swL2VlanMultiplyAdvertisement
swL2VlanMultiplyAdvertisement.description: This object specifies the advertisement state.

swL2VlanMultiplyPortListAction.name: swL2VlanMultiplyPortListAction
swL2VlanMultiplyPortListAction.description: Specifies the action for the port list which specified by swL2VlanMultiplyPortList.

swL2VlanMultiplyAction.name: swL2VlanMultiplyAction
swL2VlanMultiplyAction.description: Specifies the action for VLANs. other: no action. create: the VLANs specified by swL2VlanMultiplyVlanList would be created at a time. configure: the VLANs specified by swL2VlanMultiplyVlanList would be configured at a time. delete: the VLANs specified by swL2VlanMultiplyVlanList would be deleted at a time.

swL2DhcpLocalRelayState.name: swL2DhcpLocalRelayState
swL2DhcpLocalRelayState.description: This object indicates the status of the DHCP local relay function of the switch.

swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANTable.name: swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANTable
swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANTable.description: This table is used to manage the DHCP local relay status for each VLAN.

swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANEntry.name: swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANEntry
swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANEntry.description: This object lists the current VLANs in the switch and their corresponding DHCP local relay status.

swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANID.name: swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANID
swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANID.description: This object shows the VIDs of the current VLANS in the switch.

swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANState.name: swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANState
swL2DhcpLocalRelayVLANState.description: This object indicates the status of the DHCP relay function of the VLAN.

swL2FloodMACState.name: swL2FloodMACState
swL2FloodMACState.description: This object indicates the status of Flooding MAC function.

swL2FloodMACLogState.name: swL2FloodMACLogState
swL2FloodMACLogState.description: This object indicates whether logs are generated when a flooding MAC is detected.

swL2FloodMACTrapState.name: swL2FloodMACTrapState
swL2FloodMACTrapState.description: This object indicates whether traps are generated when a flooding MAC is detected.

swL2FloodMACClearFDB.name: swL2FloodMACClearFDB
swL2FloodMACClearFDB.description: When set to start(2), this object will clear the entries of swL2FloodMACFDBTable. After the device finishes clearing the entries, it will return to its default value, no-action(1). Setting this object to no-action(1) will not have any effect.

swL2FloodMACAutoFDBCtrlTable.name: swL2FloodMACAutoFDBCtrlTable
swL2FloodMACAutoFDBCtrlTable.description: A table containing a list of configured IP addresses to which the Auto FDB function will discover the corresponding VLAN, MAC address and port and have a corresponding static FDB entry created automatically.

swL2FloodMACAutoFDBCtrlEntry.name: swL2FloodMACAutoFDBCtrlEntry
swL2FloodMACAutoFDBCtrlEntry.description: Information containing the configured Auto FDB IP address.

swL2FloodMACAutoFDBRowStatus.name: swL2FloodMACAutoFDBRowStatus
swL2FloodMACAutoFDBRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL2FloodMACFDBTable.name: swL2FloodMACFDBTable
swL2FloodMACFDBTable.description: A table containing a list of current and historical flooding MAC entries.

swL2FloodMACFDBEntry.name: swL2FloodMACFDBEntry
swL2FloodMACFDBEntry.description: Information containing the flooding MAC address.

swL2FloodMACFDBIndex.name: swL2FloodMACFDBIndex
swL2FloodMACFDBIndex.description: The hardware address table index of the flooding MAC entry.

swL2FloodMACFDBVID.name: swL2FloodMACFDBVID
swL2FloodMACFDBVID.description: The VLAN identifier of the flooding MAC entry.

swL2FloodMACFDBMacAddress.name: swL2FloodMACFDBMacAddress
swL2FloodMACFDBMacAddress.description: The MAC address of the flooding MAC entry.

swL2FloodMACFDBStatus.name: swL2FloodMACFDBStatus
swL2FloodMACFDBStatus.description: The status of the flooding MAC entry. When the value is 'active', this means the entry is currently present in the hardware address table, otherwise, the value is 'inactive'.

swL2FloodMACFDBTimestamp.name: swL2FloodMACFDBTimestamp
swL2FloodMACFDBTimestamp.description: A number that correlates to a relative time the entry was detected by the Flooding MAC function.

swL2FloodMACAutoFDBTable.name: swL2FloodMACAutoFDBTable
swL2FloodMACAutoFDBTable.description: A table containing the discovered VLAN, MAC address and port of the host with an IP address created in swL2FloodMACAutoFDBCtrlTable.

swL2FloodMACAutoFDBEntry.name: swL2FloodMACAutoFDBEntry
swL2FloodMACAutoFDBEntry.description: Information containing the discovered VLAN, MAC address and port of an Auto FDB entry.

swL2FloodMACAutoFDBVID.name: swL2FloodMACAutoFDBVID
swL2FloodMACAutoFDBVID.description: The VLAN identifier of Auto FDB entry.

swL2FloodMACAutoFDBMacAddress.name: swL2FloodMACAutoFDBMacAddress
swL2FloodMACAutoFDBMacAddress.description: The MAC address of the Auto FDB entry.
